00:06:18.307 --> 00:06:22.732
So, so let's match the teacher's comments

00:06:22.732 --> 00:06:24.154
to the definitions.

00:06:24.154 --> 00:06:26.788
Ivy's definition: "All of the points

00:06:26.788 --> 00:06:30.331
"in line with P and Q,
extending infinitely

00:06:30.331 --> 00:06:32.098
"in both directions."

00:06:32.098 --> 00:06:34.089
Well, that would be the
definition of a line.

00:06:34.089 --> 00:06:35.786
That would be the line P, Q.

00:06:35.786 --> 00:06:37.412
That would be, if you're
extending infinitely

00:06:37.412 --> 00:06:39.999
in both directions, so ...

00:06:40.573 --> 00:06:41.966
I would say, "Are you thinking of a line

00:06:41.966 --> 00:06:44.237
"instead of a line segment?"

00:06:44.237 --> 00:06:47.691
Ethan's definition: "The
exact distance from P to Q.

00:06:47.691 --> 00:06:48.576
Well, that's just a ...

