that's the length of a line segment.

00:06:52.195 --> 00:06:54.957
That's not exactly what a line segment is.

00:06:54.957 --> 00:06:57.030
And see, Ebuka's definition.

00:06:57.030 --> 00:07:00.401
"The points P and Q, which
are called endpoints,

00:07:00.401 --> 00:07:02.067
"and all of the points in a straight line

00:07:02.067 --> 00:07:03.895
"between points P and Q.

00:07:03.895 --> 00:07:06.150
Yep. That looks like a good definition

00:07:06.150 --> 00:07:08.914
for a line segment.

00:07:08.914 --> 00:07:10.762
So we can just check our,

00:07:10.762 --> 00:07:12.536
we can just check our answer.

00:07:13.658 --> 00:07:14.776
So, looking good.

00:07:14.776 --> 00:07:15.893
Let's do one more of this.

00:07:15.893 --> 00:07:18.612
I'm just really enjoying
pretending to be a teacher.

00:07:19.348 --> 00:07:21.217
All right. "Three
students attempt to define

00:07:21.217 --> 00:07:23.046
"what a circle is."

00:07:23.046 --> 00:07:24.427
